The quality factor, Q10dB (e.g., Narins and Capranica 1976; Shofner and Feng 1981), is lower than that of other vertebrate hearing organs in the same frequency range, (Evans 1975; see Fig. 5), and ranges from approximately 1 to 2 in both the leopard frog and the bullfrog (Ronken 1991; see Fig. 5). For other anuran species, the ranges are somewhat different, with the lowest minimum values (approximately 0.5) reported for Hyla regilla, and the highest maximum values (approximately 2.8) in Scaphiopus couchi. Thus, the basilar papilla’s frequency selectivity is relatively poor. Fig. 5
